    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-12-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-12-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="257"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-12-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 13, 1898</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 659.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Referring to your instruction of the 26th ultimo
                    (No. 640), I have the honor to inform you that I have just learned from our
                    consulate at Bremen that he has already—on November 3, in an unnumbered
                    dispatch—sent to the Department a copy of the new Bremen regulations in regard
                    to the examination of living plants and fruits, to which reference was made in
                    my dispatch No. 592 of November 8.</p>
                <p>In this connection, however, I beg to inclose a copy of the Hamburg regulations
                    on the same subject, which I have this morning received from the consul at
                    Hamburg, who informs me that he has sent no copy of them to the Department, to
                    which I referred in dispatch No. 586, of November 3.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John B. Jackson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
